{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"00b7095b-dcbc-4a06-93bc-cd149cccd76b","content":"The problem is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_eCRQuAeph7sXDWyfUa4j1B","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-acd9a306c8ca4ce7b33edb4b5774ea38/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-acd9a306c8ca4ce7b33edb4b5774ea38/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"2e958268-f01b-4a70-b4b4-a0c3e3fddeca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs — depends on Domain.fs (opens BrokenOrder.Domain)\n2. Domain.fs — defines the types\n3. Program.fs — depends on both\n\nServices.fs is listed before Domain.fs, but Services.fs uses types from Domain.fs. The fix is to put Domain.fs first, then Services.fs, then Program.fs.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"DBD7:58623:15A397C:1834BA2:69FD3382"},"id":"b873730b-cbf9-4887-a846-0bd2e6607091","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:23.281Z","parentId":"91483448-3b0a-492f-ae27-ad9388512b42"}
